DEVELOPMENT LICENCE VERIFICATION KEY — NOT FOR PRODUCTION.

The public half of ops/licence/dev-signing-key.pem. It lives in a file rather than as a constant
in the TypeScript source for one reason: `apps/api/Dockerfile` copies `apps/api`, never `ops/`, so
a production image physically does not contain this key and cannot fall back to it.

That matters because the private half is committed. As a compiled-in constant, the only thing
standing between a shipped image and free Advanced was NODE_ENV — which whoever runs the container
sets. As a file, the guard is a property of the artifact instead of its configuration.

-----BEGIN PUBLIC KEY-----
MCowBQYDK2VwAyEA0odlEiChzxQPZHktyhOEAu2upMta2y73YAZrOlDY/9s=
-----END PUBLIC KEY-----
